children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"evitación de traumatismos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"68","parent":"0","text":"dermatitis herpetiforme","guid":"SHgj2nSMfAx_Wm83-BrsLw","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"General ","guid":"NHj3GDXFsWVnGSVsEwplxA","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"EAA subepidérmica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"mayoría de los pacientes tienen enfermedad celíaca","guid":"14QN4MlxNKvkJUBTbsh9gg","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"68","text":"Clinica ","guid":"p2tDNfZ7nycLAOugbGP4TA","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"extremadamente pruriginosa","guid":"B1ad5UeIzwXXyO7vi7_c_w","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"inicia en la edad adulta y persiste durante toda la vida","guid":"leUqjIa7VRC-mH7qA14zOg","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"pequeñas pápulas y vesículas tensas, que rara vez están intactas","guid":"746-KXeHcmwNscmirNnckw","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"agrupadas de forma característica","guid":"JO3rEVgE4jE5HEyqxdODWA","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"72","text":"excoriaciones  cuero cabelludo, codos, rodillas, espalda y glúteos","guid":"w4UHYYPJlZtt2JhgsHqKkA","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"68","text":"Diagnóstico ","guid":"oYGHYNeR42r5V3wdtytNlQ","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"biopsia cutánea para pruebas rutinarias e inmunofluorescencia directa","guid":"unSWfPjpv99AiLvW2Vcksw","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"78","text":"sedimentación de IgA granular en las puntas de las papilas\\Ndérmicas es patognomónica de dermatitis herpetiforme","guid":"2t_3YgvrIFqdhC66jU7VZQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"68","text":"tratamiento","guid":"e1nhdELzOrzNHtI9r2SSCQ","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"dieta sin gluten","guid":"ReGY_4n-LNhhGc12aZ0UOQ","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"tratamiento adicional\\Ncon dapsona","guid":"jrcajtwsMPo2_20PQm9JoQ","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Antes de iniciar la terapia con dapsona, los pacientes deberían ser evaluados\\Npara detectar un posible déficit de glucosa-6-fosfato deshidrogenasa.","guid":"XiqTOOF0WgzXjCLzXgY3YA","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"alto riesgo de hemólisis durante la terapia con dapsona","guid":"VqVyPOWXlKr3HrrBfHp5Ug","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"0","text":"tratamiento","guid":"NPxBOLeMRE5I6Td2HWYbtg","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"General ","guid":"R9xKAfMas0JY5Fh5eVqiYA","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"depende de los síntomas, la extensión de la\\Nenfermedad y las comorbilidades asociadas","guid":"ojwsm594nc5MIvH80KSzKw","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"enfermedad\\Nlocalizada","guid":"oPMIZfTIPgmvIQKalt0ixg","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"glucocorticoides tópicos o intralesionales pueden ser suficientes","guid":"Mtp9C-PMjIar5kuBGZc_BA","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"infección bacteriana secundaria puede dar lugar a exacerbación","guid":"Ded1m6z-fpAW3_gbZPUUlQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"86","text":"EAA","guid":"QOHyDOuruYLqKw8-neGP8Q","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"General ","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"no están aprobados por la FDA, y las\\Nrecomendaciones se basan en la opinión de expertos","guid":"2mqjzGapCofest6J68_S_g","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"objetivo es reducir los anticuerpos circulantes, con la posterior eliminación de\\Nlos anticuerpos fijados a antígenos cutáneos y la restauración de la función","guid":"_srTJgdURLryR8uwKZwwTQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"92","text":"1","guid":"gAMdp4aA8tjgLWKxWvwmDQ","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"prednisona hasta que no aparezcan\\Nnuevas vesículas o ampollas","guid":"OlLr2alZ8YHsyf72WOJMqg","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"92","text":"2","guid":"dD4eLpcHLatNXSshZHGHqA","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":